definition.value: A branched amino decasaccharide consisting of a linear heptasaccharide comprising N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine and beta-D-galactose residues, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (2->3), (1->3), (1->4), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the galactose residue proximal to the reducing end also carries an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residue via a (1->3) linkage and the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear octasaccharide comprising two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residues, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine and beta-D-galactose residues, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (2->8), (2->3), (1->3), (1->4), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the galactose residue proximal to the reducing end also carries an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residue via a (1->3) linkage and the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.

A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of a linear hexasaccharide comprising two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residues, a beta-D-galactose residue, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (2->8), (2->3), (1->3),(1->3), (1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.

A branched amino nonasaccharide consisting of a linear pentasaccharide comprising N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, beta-D-galactose, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (1->4), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the galactose residue also carries an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->8)-N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid unit via a (2->3) linkage and the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.
A furancarboxylate that is the conjugate base of 2-furoic acid.
